  }, "Absorption rates (biology, geology, chemistry)"), mdx("p", null, "There is a natural limit to how fast something can grow, governed by how fast it can absorb certain nutrients. But different organisms have massively different absorption rates despite being delivered nutrients at the same rate, so you can get vastly different outcomes despite feeding something the same nutrients. Same with education, career success, and social networks -- some people are primed to absorb much more than others, even when they are part of the same system."), mdx("h2", {
