    "id": "three-men-make-a-tiger-chinese-proverb"
  }, "Three Men Make a Tiger (Chinese proverb)"), mdx("p", null, "If one person tells you there's a tiger roaming around your neighborhood, you can assume they're lying. If two people tell you, you begin to wonder. If three say it's true, you're convinced there's a tiger in your neighborhood and you run for your life. The proverb first came about hundreds of years ago, but is probably more relevant than ever in the social media age. People will believe anything if enough people tell them it's true."));
